main event: A pilot observed a round object approximately 100-200 feet in diameter performing unusual maneuvers over Rosalia, Washington on February 1, 1953.
interesting points: The object displayed rapid acceleration and abrupt changes in direction., The pilot's visual observations were corroborated by radar data., The object was reported to be under control and maneuvering intentionally., The sighting lasted for about 20 minutes., All pilots involved agreed there was no known aircraft or meteor at the time.
